import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = pd.cut(data['distance'], bins=[0, 500, 1000, 1500, 2000, np.inf], labels=['0-500', '501-1000', '1001-1500', '1501-2000', '2000+'])
    delay_by_distance = data.groupby('distance_range')['delay'].mean()
    ax = delay_by_distance.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axhline(y=delay_by_distance.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Delay Time')
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance Range')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Delay Time')
    ax.set_title('What is the average delay time for flights of different distances?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
